's keep it simple and just focus on ensuring everything's in order before taking that step.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Added a dedicated test for the active dynamic-access class:\n\n- `tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15to18/1.77/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15to18/BCSNTRUPrimePrivateKeyTest.java`\n\nThe test creates a `BCSNTRUPrimePrivateKey` through Bouncy Castle’s public JCA `KeyPairGenerator`, serializes it with `ObjectOutputStream`, deserializes it with `ObjectInputStream`, and verifies the restored key preserves format, parameter spec, encoding, equality, and hash code. This should exercise the remaining `writeObject` and `readObject` dynamic-access call sites for `BCSNTRUPrimePrivateKey`.\n\nPer instructions, I did not run tests locally.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_03aa07fe1cf6e160016a264dd1c8ec8190aa518fc6da099d3c\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2034, "output": 723, "cacheRead": 36352, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 39109, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1780895168283, "responseId": "resp_03aa07fe1cf6e160016a264dc0fcbc81908ce24f13b76da316"}}
